        <!-- Overview Tab -->
        <div id="overview" class="tab-content active">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Quick Start</h2>
                <p>The timer application consists of two main interfaces:</p>
                
                <div class="quick-links">
                    <a href="/" class="quick-link" target="_blank">
                        Timer Display<br>
                        <small>Full-screen countdown view</small>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/control" class="quick-link" target="_blank">
                        Control Panel<br>
                        <small>Start, pause, and reset timer</small>
                    </a>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Full-screen display</strong> - Perfect for presentations and public viewing</li>
                    <li><strong>Responsive design</strong> - Works on all screen sizes from mobile to large displays</li>
                    <li><strong>Offline resilience</strong> - Continues running even if connection is lost</li>
                    <li><strong>Visual alerts</strong> - Warning colors and flashing when time expires</li>
                    <li><strong>Count-up mode</strong> - Timer continues counting up after reaching zero (default)</li>
                    <li><strong>Target time countdown</strong> - Count down to a specific date and time</li>
                    <li><strong>Access control</strong> - IP whitelisting for timer controls</li>
                    <li><strong>Customizable appearance</strong> - Colors, fonts, and display options</li>
                    <li><strong>Flexible positioning</strong> - Place timer in any corner or center of screen</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>Tip:</strong> Anyone can view the timer display, but only whitelisted IPs can control it (start/pause/reset).
                </div>

                <h3>Control Panel Modes</h3>
                <p>The control panel (<code>/control</code>) offers two modes for starting timers:</p>

                <h4>Duration Mode</h4>
                <p>Set a timer for a specific duration (hours, minutes, seconds). Use the preset buttons for quick access to common durations.</p>

                <h4>Target Time Mode</h4>
                <p>Set a timer to count down to a specific date and time. Perfect for events, deadlines, or scheduled activities. The timer automatically calculates and updates the remaining time until the target.</p>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> The control panel always shows count-up behavior (displays time past zero as +00:00:01, etc.). The timer display clients can choose to stop at zero using the <code>?stop-at-zero=true</code> parameter.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
